[
    {
        "content": "<p>To go along with replacing backslash closure syntax with ||-delimited closure args, what if we also did the same to types?</p>\n<p>i.e. instead of writing <code>Str, Str -&gt; Str</code>, you write <code>|Str, Str| Str</code>.</p>\n<p>That brings a nice syntactic symmetry with the implementation:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>foo: |Str, Str| Str\nfoo = |a, b| &quot;Hello ${a} and ${b}&quot;\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>And, as a side-note, it resolves a long frustrating part of the parser: parsing function types in tuples / tag unions / records. When done with lookahead and/or backtracking (as is currently done), this can lead to exponential behavior in the parser. It's possible to parse without backtracking, but the parser gets rather messy.</p>",
        "id": 491000307,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1735311724
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>we definitely need <code>-&gt;</code> or <code>=&gt;</code> in the type! <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 491001284,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735312310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the arrow still works with this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"kt\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Str</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Str</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"Hello ${a} and ${b}\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491001417,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735312395
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just for my OCD:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elixir\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"nc\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Str</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Str</span>\n<span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Hello ${a} and ${b}\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491001554,
        "sender_full_name": "Georges Boris",
        "timestamp": 1735312490
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this is an interesting idea to me for a different reason than the ones discussed so far: the current function type syntax doesn't have an obvious way to represent a zero-arg function, but this actually would!</p>",
        "id": 491001769,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735312629
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>can someone get me up to speed why the <code>!</code> at the end of the name is not enough already to signify side effects? (I'm guessing for stuff like standalone types)</p>",
        "id": 491001816,
        "sender_full_name": "lue",
        "timestamp": 1735312675
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"522669\">lue</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/Switch.20function.20types.20to.20use.20vertical.20bars/near/491001816\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>can someone get me up to speed why the <code>!</code> at the end of the name is not enough already to signify side effects? (I'm guessing for stuff like standalone types)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, exactly that.</p>",
        "id": 491001885,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735312700
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah, like for example anonymous functions and types of functions that take other functions as arguments</p>",
        "id": 491001919,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735312731
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <code>|...| -&gt; ...</code> could be nice</p>",
        "id": 491009635,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735318025
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if we do that, I realized they actually can be nested in types without parens</p>",
        "id": 491035150,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735336113
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491035214,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735336185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>because <code>|</code> only ends the args list if it's followed by either <code>-&gt;</code> or <code>=&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 491035304,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735336233
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>otherwise it's opening a nested function type</p>",
        "id": 491035327,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735336258
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>although I don't love how that looks <span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 491035433,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735336335
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh yeah....didn't think about nesting...works but is not as nice as parents for readability</p>",
        "id": 491035760,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735336609
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anything nested should have proper open/close brace pairs as delimiters</p>",
        "id": 491036355,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735337067
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491036791,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735337445
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>today:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491036965,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735337612
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>today definitely looks nicest to me <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 491037171,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735337765
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for higher order function types</p>",
        "id": 491037178,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735337775
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If only the lambda syntax could also match the current type annotations... oh wait <span aria-label=\"grimacing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f62c\" role=\"img\" title=\"grimacing\">:grimacing:</span></p>",
        "id": 491038993,
        "sender_full_name": "Georges Boris",
        "timestamp": 1735339364
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>there is the question of how the current syntax would represent the type of a function with no arguments</p>",
        "id": 491039673,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735339934
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>one possibility:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">run!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">run!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">||</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># ...</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491039708,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735339982
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why don’t we just do parens around args? It would match the calling syntax </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">run!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491042028,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1735342226
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Tbh I don't dislike that. It may look unexpected the first time but I don't see how this could be interpreted as anything other than 0-arg function.</p>\n<p>It would be great to actually ask someone.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elixir\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\"># this means a function that takes two numbers and returns a number</span>\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Num</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># this one takes one number and returns a string</span>\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Str</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># what does this mean?</span>\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Str</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491042039,
        "sender_full_name": "Georges Boris",
        "timestamp": 1735342238
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"489294\">Agus Zubiaga</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/Switch.20function.20types.20to.20use.20vertical.20bars/near/491042028\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Why don’t we just do parens around args? It would match the calling syntax </p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">run!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>in that design, wouldn't the first one need nested parens?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491042209,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735342396
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>True</p>",
        "id": 491042223,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1735342416
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Looks fine, though</p>",
        "id": 491042239,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1735342441
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>imho the extra noise for 99% of type annotations doesn't outweigh the perhaps weird first of impression of <code>fn : =&gt; {}</code></p>",
        "id": 491042452,
        "sender_full_name": "Georges Boris",
        "timestamp": 1735342622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>another scenario that doesn't look great with bars in the types: multiline args <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span> </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">parse_user_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Request</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Jwt</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Secret</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Instant</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">UserId</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">MissingTokenHeader</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">InvalidJwt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Jwt</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ParseErr</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">parse_user_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">jwt_secret</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491050912,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735351346
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>with the parens idea it could be:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">parse_user_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Request</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Jwt</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Secret</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Instant</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">UserId</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">MissingTokenHeader</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">InvalidJwt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Jwt</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ParseErr</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">parse_user_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">jwt_secret</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491050983,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735351438
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>today:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">parse_user_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Request</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Jwt</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Secret</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Instant</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">UserId</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">MissingTokenHeader</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">InvalidJwt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Jwt</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ParseErr</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">parse_user_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">jwt_secret</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491051037,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735351473
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Today looks great!</p>",
        "id": 491051047,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735351496
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd only lean towards circle brackets for alignment with our function defs, but since they're different brackets, I don't think its worth it</p>",
        "id": 491051095,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735351559
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>parse_user_id :  |\n    Request,\n    Jwt.Secret,\n    Instant,\n    | -&gt; Result UserId [MissingTokenHeader, InvalidJwt Jwt.ParseErr]\nparse_user_id = |req, jwt_secret, now|\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491065337,
        "sender_full_name": "Karl",
        "timestamp": 1735366751
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Parens make it look like the function takes a tuple to me</p>",
        "id": 491074437,
        "sender_full_name": "Kilian Vounckx",
        "timestamp": 1735375401
    }
]